h2. Bean 'historyService'

You can use the *[org.camunda.bpm.engine.HistoryService|http://docs.camunda.org/latest/api-references/javadoc/org/camunda/bpm/engine/HistoryService.html]* as an injectable bean:

{code}
def historyService
{code}

The plugin registers the bean as 'camundaHistoryServiceBean' with the default alias 'historyService'.
You can change this default alias via [configuration|guide:bean-names].